&lt;h3 id="mid-server"&gt;Default MID Server&lt;/h3&gt;&#13;
&lt;p&gt;For on-site Tanium instances, setting this system property will override the configured mid server for any REST messages being used (if one is specified on the REST Method record). &lt;br /&gt;&#13;
If you use TaaS, you can leave this property blank.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;
&lt;p&gt;This property should be set to the NAME of the MID server to use, not the sys_id.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;
&lt;strong&gt;Default&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;i&gt;(none)&lt;/i&gt;</description>
